    • Enum Constant Detail

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final Mutability UNKNOWN
        Mutability is not known; probably value can be mutated

      • MUTABLE

        public static final Mutability MUTABLE
        A value is known to be mutable (e.g. elements are sometimes added to the collection)

      • UNMODIFIABLE_VIEW

        public static final Mutability UNMODIFIABLE_VIEW
        A value is known to be an immutable view over a possibly mutable value: it cannot be mutated directly using this reference; however subsequent reads (e.g. Collection.size()) may return different results if the underlying value is mutated by somebody else.

      • UNMODIFIABLE

        public static final Mutability UNMODIFIABLE
        A value is known to be immutable. For collection no elements could be added, removed or altered (though if collection contains mutable elements, they still could be mutated).

      • getMutability

        public static Mutability getMutability(PsiModifierListOwner owner)
        Returns a mutability of the supplied element, if known. The element could be a method (in this case the return value mutability is returned), a method parameter (the returned mutability will reflect whether the method can mutate the parameter), or a field (in this case the mutability could be obtained from its initializer).
        Parameters:
        owner - an element to check the mutability
        Returns:
        a Mutability enum value; UNKNOWN if cannot be determined or specified element type is not supported.
